==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Theologize
<hw>The*ol"o*gize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Theologized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Theologizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>th⟦eacute⟧ologiser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To render theological; to
apply to divinity; to reduce to a system of theology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>School divinity was but Aristotle's philosophy
<qex>theologized</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theologize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Theologize
<hw>The*ol"o*gize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To frame a system of
theology; to theorize or speculate upon theological subjects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theologizer</ent>⟦br⟧
